title: Kirksville cross country runs at Mexico Autumn Classic
text: Kirksville cross country runs at Mexico Autumn Classic Comment Kirksville Daily Express - Kirksville, MO Writer Posted Oct. 20, 2015 at 9:17 PM Posted Oct. 20, 2015 at 9:17 PM HIGHSCHOOLCROSS COUNTRY Kirksville at Mexico Autumn Classic Girls - Erica Wollmering, 8th place finish, 21:52; Lauren Gaines, 18th place finish, 23:09; Yordie Schneider, 22nd place finish, 24:05; Emily Eital, 38th place finish, 26:04; Skylar Kertz, 6th place JVfinish, 25:07; Emma Bushnell, 11th place JVfinish, 25:53; Skylar Petersen, 34th place JVfinish, 30:38 Boys - Duncan Clark, 2nd place finish, 16:33; Parker Petersen, 30th place finish, 20:25; Nolon Carter, 2nd place JVfinish, 19:38; Garrett Johnson, 9th place JVfinish, 20:52; Curtis Burgeon, 12th place JVfinish, 21:11; Sam Tiedeman, 17th place JVfinish, 21:47; Ryan Everett, 26th place JVfinish, 23:57 “Ifelt really felt good about our JVkids because they stepped in and ran the same course and competed well,” Kirksville coach Geoff Hutton said. “We’ve just got to get back to training. We have until next week to fine tune some things and get ready for districts.” Kirksville Daily Express - Kirksville, MO Writer
